claw, the GTK-based Microraptor client.">
<h2>Claw's Keyboard Shortcut Reference</h2>

<div class="content">We have made a concerted effort to provide
reasonably intuitive key bindings for as many Claw commands as
possible.  All of Claw's functionality is available through the main
menu bar, and key bindings are displayed within the menus as a
reminder.  The rather unintuitive bindings of some of these options
are forced by the hardcoded bindings in the entry widget (used to
provide input to processes' stdin), since we avoid conflicts so as to
make the keybindings consistent throughout the program.  Note that
much of this functionality is also available in the context menus
(i.e. right-click menus).</div>

<center>
<table class="content" border="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
      <td class="head">Shortcut</td>
      <td class="headLeft">Description</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+R</b></td>
      <td>Run currently selected process(es) <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+T</b></td>
      <td>Terminate (kill) currently selected process(es) <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+S</b></td>
      <td>Show (view) currently selected process(es) <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+M</b></td>
      <td>Mask (hide) currently selected process(es) <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+O</b></td>
      <td>Switch to Overview tab (shows all currently viewed
      processes' output)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+Y</b></td>
      <td>Update status of currently selected process(es) <a
      href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a>.  Note that this will have little to no
      effect in most cases; Claw now automatically updates process
      state every 30 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="bottomLine">
      <td colspan="2" class="bottomLine">For the above shortcuts, Shift+Ctrl+key performs
      the given action for all known processes, rather than the
      currently selected ones.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+Tab</b></td>
      <td>Switch to the next tab in the process interaction area (note
      that this will change the currently selected process, unless the
      <a
      href="index.html.page=docs.config.claw#tieSelToTab">tie
      seletion to tab</a> Claw preference has been changed to '0').</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+Shift+Tab</b></td>
      <td>Switch to the previous tab in the process interaction area
      (note that this will change the currently selected process,
      unless the <a
      href="index.html.page=docs.config.claw#tieSelToTab">tie
      seletion to tab</a> Claw preference has been changed to
      '0').</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+L</b></td>
      <td>Listen (subscribe to) currently selected process(es) output <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+N</b></td>
      <td>u(N)subscribe from currently selected process(es) output <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Alt+M</b></td>
      <td>Clear the current process' output buffer (this is equivalent
      to <span class="ic">clear</span> in an xterm).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+G</b></td>
      <td>Set process confi(G)uration for currently selected process <a href="index.html.page=docs.claw.keys#curSel">[*]</a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+I</b></td>
      <td>Load configuration file stored on cl(I)ent machine</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+J</b></td>
      <td>Reload most recently loaded client-local config file.  This
      reloads from disk, and will thus pick up any changes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Shft+Ctrl+I</b></td>
      <td>Load a configuration file stored on a daemon machine</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+Z</b></td>

      <td>Swallow an arbitrary X window into a tab (after selecting
      this, your mouse cursor will change; the next window you click
      on will be swallowed).  You may later unswallow it; this
      provides a simple way to avoid screen clutter and bring all
      system components together.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+P</b></td>
      <td>Open the claw preferences dialog</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+Q</b></td>
      <td>Quit the client</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td colspan="2" class="topLine">Within the entry line for a given process, most
      Emacs-ish keybindings hold (since they're hard-coded into the
      GTK widget, they force some of the (rather non-intuitive)
      bindings above):</td>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+A</b></td>
      <td>Go to beginning of line</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+B</b></td>
      <td>Move back one character</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+C</b></td>
      <td>Copy to clipboard</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+D</b></td>
      <td>Delete forward one character</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+E</b></td>
      <td>Move to end of line</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+F</b></td>
      <td>Move forward one character</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+H</b></td>
      <td>Delete backward one character</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+K</b></td>
      <td>Delete from cursor to end of line</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+U</b></td>
      <td>Delete line</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+V</b></td>
      <td>Paste from clipboard</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+W</b></td>
      <td>Delete backward one word</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Ctrl+X</b></td>
      <td>Cut to clipboard</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Alt+B</b></td>
      <td>Move backward one word</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Alt+D</b></td>
      <td>Delete forward one word</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
      <td class="shortCell"><b>Alt+F</b></td>
      <td>Move forward one word</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</center>

<a name="curSel"> <div class="content"><b>[*] Note:</b> "currently
selected process(es)" refers to the zero or more processes highlighted
in the process tree widget in the upper-left pane of the GUI.</div>
